0post%20he%20coauthored%2C%20Inserra%20argued%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20First%20Amendment%20does%20protect%20misinformation%20and%20hate%20speech.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInserra%20previously%20spent%20nearly%20eight%20years%20at%20the%20Heritage%20Foundation%20as%20a%20policy%20analyst%20focused%20on%20homeland%20security%20and%20cyber%20policy.%20In%202023%20%E2%80%94%20after%20Inserra%20left%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Heritage%20Foundation%20published%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-project-2025-conservative-political-playbook-heritage-foundation-trump-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EProject%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20900-plus-page%20conservative%20policy%20agenda%20that%20includes%20proposals%20to%20eliminate%20the%20Department%20of%20Education%20and%20restrict%20federal%20efforts%20to%20combat%20misinformation.%20On%20LinkedIn%2C%20he%20describes%20himself%20as%20an%20%26quot%3BAdvocate%20for%20free%20expression%20online.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorbin%20Barthold%2C%20internet%20policy%20counsel%20and%20director%20of%20appellate%20litigation%20at%20TechFreedom%2C%20also%20joined%20the%20council.%20TechFreedom%20is%20a%20libertarian-leaning%20think%20tank%20focused%20on%20tech%20policy.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EBarthold%20has%20been%20critical%20of%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20policies%20and%20outspoken%20against%20efforts%20to%20ban%20TikTok%2C%20especially%20the%20national%20security%20rationale%20behind%20it.%20In%20a%20January%20post%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fcorbinkbarthold%2Fstatus%2F1875653186943643848%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20wrote%3A%20%26quot%3B'National%20security'%20in%20this%20context%20is%20code%20for%20'afraid%20of%20speech.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20new%20member%20is%20Desmond%20Upton%20Patton%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.asc.upenn.edu%2Fpeople%2Ffaculty%2Fdesmond-upton-patton-msw-phd%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%2